n nach wie vor nur sporadisch bei der Entwicklung und Umsetzung von DaZ-Förderkonzepten berücksichtigt. Die Beiträge des vorliegenden Sammelbandes vereint das Anliegen, diese Kluft zwischen linguistischer und didaktischer DaZ-Forschung zu überbrücken und auf Grundlage theoretischer und empirischer Forschungsergebnisse konkrete Impulse für die Konzeption von Sprachförderung zu liefern.  aKnowledge derived from linguistics and language acquisition research is still only sporadically translated to programs for teaching German as a second language. The papers in this collection attempt to bridge the gap between linguistic and educational research about German as a second language and to apply the findings of theoretical and empirical research to develop concrete suggestions for the design of language programs.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGerman languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakersvCongresses. 0aLanguage acquisitionvCongresses. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teachingvCongresses. 4aPsycholinguistik. 4aSprachdidaktik. 4aSprachförderung. 4aZweitspracherwerb. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aSecond language acquisition, language promotion, language didactics, psycholinguistics.1 aAguado, Karin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrede, Julia Ricart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBryant, Doreen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerwien, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaberzettl, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlages, Hana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlages, Hana, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.go